dataSets.name: Data Set 1
dataSets.description: FBI investigative files, flight logs, contact books, and early case documents from the Palm Beach investigation (2005-2008)

dataSets.name: Data Set 2
dataSets.description: FBI 302 interview reports, police reports from Palm Beach, and early correspondence between Epstein's legal team and federal prosecutors

dataSets.name: Data Set 3
dataSets.description: FBI investigative files including victim statements, witness interviews, and law enforcement correspondence

dataSets.name: Data Set 4
dataSets.description: FBI Form 302 interview summaries documenting victim statements and recruitment patterns at Epstein's properties

dataSets.name: Data Set 5
dataSets.description: Grand jury transcripts, SDNY investigation documents, and indictment materials from the 2019 federal case

dataSets.name: Data Set 6
dataSets.description: Search warrant applications, property inventories from FBI raids on Manhattan mansion, Palm Beach estate, and private island

dataSets.name: Data Set 7
dataSets.description: Financial records including wire transfers, bank statements, and property transaction documents

dataSets.name: Data Set 8
dataSets.description: Surveillance footage summaries, MCC records, property records for Little St. James Island, and death investigation materials

dataSets.name: Data Set 9
dataSets.description: High-value communication records: private email correspondence between Epstein and prominent individuals, internal DOJ correspondence regarding the 2008 NPA

dataSets.name: Data Set 10
dataSets.description: Visual and forensic media: 180,000+ images and 2,000+ videos seized from Epstein's properties. Female faces redacted for victim protection

dataSets.name: Data Set 11
dataSets.description: Financial ledgers, additional flight manifests beyond previously published logs, and property seizure records

dataSets.name: Data Set 12
dataSets.description: Supplemental and late productions: approximately 150 documents requiring prolonged legal review, released January 30, 2026

dataSets.name: Court Records - Giuffre v. Maxwell
dataSets.description: Judicial records from Giuffre v. Maxwell civil case (No. 1:15-cv-07433), unsealed throughout 2024-2025 by Judge Loretta Preska. Organized by docket number.

dataSets.name: FOIA Records
dataSets.description: Records released under standard Freedom of Information Act requests prior to the Transparency Act. Often contain heavy prior redactions.
